Vice President Joe Biden and Dr. Jill Biden released a statement expressing their condolences for the shooting of two police officers in Des Moines, Iowa. They highlighted the bravery and dedication of Sergeant Anthony Beminio and Officer Justin Martin, who were killed in the line of duty. The Bidens also praised the swift response of the police chiefs and their teams, as well as the unity and support shown by the community. They emphasized that even in the face of tragedy, the nation is defined by goodness and the heroism of law enforcement officers. The statement concluded with prayers for the fallen officers and their families, as well as a plea for the protection of law enforcement personnel across the country.